        <comment>
  <id>119214448</id>
  <body><![CDATA[Like or unlike something is personal choice.<br /><br />But one can find some deep messages in this book:<br /><br />Fate:<br />"What’s the world’s greatest lie?<br />It’s this: that at a certain point in our lives, we lose control of what’s happening to us, and our lives become controlled by fate<br />That’s the world’s greatest lie"<br /><br />Self-Realization:<br />"There comes a time when our personal calling is so deeply buried in our soul as to be invisible. But it’s still there"<br /><br />God:<br />"I couldn’t have found God in the seminary, he thought, as he looked at the sunrise"<br /><br />Intuition:<br />"Intuition is really a sudden immersion of the soul into the universal current of life, where the histories of all people are connected, and we are able to know everything, because it’s all written there"<br /><br />Love:<br />"It was love. Something older than humanity, more ancient than the desert.... It was the pure Language of the World"<br /><br />--<br /><br />Yet there are some theories introduced by this book which just are the invention of author's mind and only superstitious will take them seriously like:<br /><br />"When you really want something, it’s because that desire originated in the soul of the universe" <br /><br />or<br /><br />"Everyone on earth has a treasure that awaits him"<br /><br />--<br /><br />Theory is something which is always true. But above two ones click for some, like a lottery, we know only few will win but a lot of people participate in it.]]></body>
  
